    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-29T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. Have acted upon your 116, September 27. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                    given me the assurance that the Argentine Government before taking any action
                    having in view the recognition of the Bolivian Government will communicate
                    further with the Government of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
